## Technical notes

<%= embed OpPrimer::ExpandableTextComponentPreview, :playground, panels: %i[params source] %>

The private `expandable-text` Stimulus controller (for `ExpandableTextComponent` only):

- Uses `ResizeObserver` (via `stimulus-use`) to reactively detect when content overflows its container
- **Horizontal:** compares `scrollWidth > clientWidth` on the `.Truncate-text` element
- **Vertical:** compares `scrollHeight > clientHeight` on the truncation target (works with `-webkit-line-clamp`)
- Toggles `Truncate--expanded` (horizontal) or `op-vertical-truncate--expanded` (vertical) CSS class for inline expansion
- Updates `aria-label` and `aria-expanded` for accessibility

